title: Kourtney embraces a tattooed mystery man
text:
This star's Valentines may have been her family this year, but that does not mean she is wanting for male attention.
Kourtney Kardashian was spotted getting a big hug from a tattooed mystery man on Thursday.
While no doubt a friend, the inked up hunk made the 37-year-old smile from ear-to-ear as she arrived at a Los Angeles studio.
Come here you: Kourtney Kardashian was spotted getting a big hug from a tattooed mystery man in Los Angeles, California, on Thursday
And no one could blame the man for wanting to give the Keeping Up With The Kardashians star a hug as she was looking great in a casually cool ensemble.
For her day at the studio, Kourt wore the current must-have style of a leather coat, an over-sized shearling-lined jacket.
The mom of three wore the trendy jacket with a pair of jeans with raw ripped hems and velvet boots.
The star further accessorized her look by wearing a black Yeezus cap from her brother-in-law Kanye West's collection.
Happy days: While no doubt a friend, the inked up hunk made the 37-year-old smile from ear-to-ear as she arrived at a Los Angeles studio
Looking good: And no one could blame the man for wanting to give the Keeping Up With The Kardashians star a hug as she was looking great in a casually cool ensemble
Kourtney did attend Kanye's show in New York Fashion Week on Wednesday, instead staying at home and looking after his and Kim Kardashian's daughter North.
While she may have not been in New York, she was thinking about her sister Kim as she shipped long stemmed red roses to her for Valentine's Day.
Kourt also got something for Valentine's Day from her sister Khloe.

Denim diva: The mom of three wore the trendy jacket with a pair of jeans with raw ripped hems and velvet boots

The card read: 'You are my Mary Kate to my Ashley. The Whitney to my Bobby. The milk to my cereal. I love you more than working out and Kit Kat.'
While Kourtney has previously been linked to Justin Bieber she has not had a public relationship since she split with Scott Disick.
She and Scoot share three children Mason, 7, Penelope, 4, and Reign, 2.
Sweet sibling: This year sister Khloe was Kourtney's Valentine sending her a lovely note
